subSubSection.paragraph:
Eunephthya maldivensis Hickson, 1905: 824, fig. 12 (Maldives, Kolumadula Atoll);
Kuekenthal 1907
: 380.

The polyps have small rodlets and spindles, situated in the tentacles and both the lateral and abaxial parts of the polyp (Figure 46
A-B
). Length of the spindles up to 0.25 mm.

Interior base of stalk. Spindles with widely spaced simple tubercles (Figure 47
B-D
); some spindles branched; some smaller ones almost smooth; many with blunt ends. The interior spindles are up to 0.85 mm long.
